        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "FAQPage",
        "mainEntity": [
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is the Express Entry CRS calculator?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "The Express Entry CRS (Comprehensive Ranking System) calculator is a free online tool that estimates your CRS score based on your age, education, language test results (IELTS, CELPIP, TEF, TCF), Canadian and foreign work experience, job offer, and provincial nomination. The maximum CRS score is 1,200 points."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is a good CRS score for Canada PR in 2026?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "A CRS score of 470 or above is generally competitive for all-program Express Entry draws in 2026. Recent IRCC draw cutoffs have ranged from 470 to 525. French-language and PNP draws often have lower cutoffs, sometimes below 400."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How is the CRS score calculated?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "CRS score is calculated across four sections: (A) Core human capital — age, education, first and second language, Canadian work experience; (B) Spouse/common-law partner factors; (C) Skill transferability factors combining education, language, and foreign work experience; (D) Additional points for provincial nomination (+600), valid job offer (+50 or +200), French language proficiency, Canadian education, and sibling in Canada (+15)."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Can I calculate CRS score without IRCC login?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Yes. This free CRS calculator requires no IRCC account, no login, and no personal information. All calculations run locally in your browser and no data is stored or transmitted."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How many CRS points does a provincial nomination add?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "A provincial nomination (PNP) adds 600 CRS points instantly, virtually guaranteeing an Invitation to Apply (ITA) in the next Express Entry draw."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How does IELTS score affect CRS points?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "IELTS scores are converted to Canadian Language Benchmark (CLB) levels before being applied to CRS. A CLB 9+ in all four skills (approximately IELTS 7.0+) earns the maximum language points. Higher IELTS scores yield higher CRS points, especially for the first official language."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is the CRS score for FSW (Federal Skilled Worker)?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Federal Skilled Worker (FSW) candidates use the same CRS scoring system as other Express Entry streams. However, FSW candidates must also meet the 67-point FSW eligibility criteria separately from the CRS score. FSW-specific draws have had cutoffs around 490–530 in recent rounds."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Does the CRS calculator work for CEC applicants?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Yes. Canadian Experience Class (CEC) applicants use this same CRS calculator. CEC candidates typically score higher due to Canadian work experience bonuses. Recent CEC-specific draw cutoffs have ranged from 430 to 500."
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "@type": "HowTo",
        "name": "How to Calculate Your CRS Score for Canada Express Entry",
        "description": "Step-by-step guide to calculating your Comprehensive Ranking System (CRS) score for Canada Express Entry using this free calculator.",
